        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 9:16PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 915 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dryburg, or near Clover, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chase City, Boydton, Kells Corner, Fairview, Rogers Corner, Spanish
Grove, Finchley, Finneywood, Skipwith, and John H Kerr Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
